      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Beware, <code>BooleanUtils</code> is still wrong (although less so than <code>Boolean</code> methods), as it will not throw exception if the value neither recognized as <code>true</code>, or <code>false</code>. So <code>ture</code> (a typo that someone does somewhere) is still blindly assumed to mean <code>false</code>. I can&#39;t find anything in Guava either (like there&#39;s no <code>Booleans.stringConverter</code> as of 23.0)."
